# Loom Steering

- At session start, read `.kiro/steering/loom-core.md` and `.kiro/steering/loom-progress.md` before doing substantive work.
- Treat `.kiro/steering/loom-progress.md` as the project handoff source of truth over chat summaries.
- Update `.kiro/steering/loom-progress.md` whenever milestones, decisions, blockers, or next steps change.
- Always refresh `.kiro/steering/loom-progress.md` before summarizing, handing off, clearing context, or ending a long session.
- Keep the progress tracker concise: replace stale status instead of appending noisy session logs.
- Preserve Loom architectural rules: no guessing on ASAM/AUTOSAR facts, no mock migration data, and always keep provenance.
